Left as an exercise.
</p>
</solution>
</example>
<example xml:id="eg_cube">
<title>Rotational symmetries of a tetrahedron</title>
<statement>
<p>
Let <m>C</m> be a cube in <m>\R^3</m> and let <m>G</m> be the group of rotational symmetries of <m>C</m>. Establish an isomorphism between <m>G</m> and one of our familiar groups. 
